      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "hey i've been struggling with my sourdough lately. i keep my starter at a steady 75f but the rise is really inconsistent. sometimes it's super bubbly and other times it's just flat. can u explain why the yeast and bacteria might be acting up even if the temp is constant?",
